  "text": "A standard result from an application of Gauss's law [CITATION_1] gives the following result for the magnitude of the electric field inside a large (compared to the thickness a), uniformly charged slab of positive charge where ρ is the volume charge density, ε 1 (= k 1 ε 0 ) is the dielectric permittivity of the slab, and x = 0 at the plane of symmetry in the center of the large rectangular slab. (Note that previously in (3), x = 0 at the left boundary of the kinetochore, Fig. 1 ).",
